The paper deals with the computational capabilities of chemical reaction networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and chemistry. The paper specifically focuses on the deterministic computation of functions using CRNs, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of CRNs in synthetic biology, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces the notion of semilinear sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper uses algorithms to analyze the computational capabilities of CRNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
